<collectingCountry box="[1146,1210,1593,1619]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, M." box="[1226,1343,1592,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" pagination="473 - 499" refId="ref5056" refString="Ono, M. (1960) Studies on Heterotropa and its related genera with special reference to their karyo-morphology and phylogeny. Journal of the Faculty of Science of University Tokyo, sec. 3, Bot. 7: 473 - 499." type="journal article" year="1960">Ono 1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yuasa, H. &amp; Maekawa, F." pageId="1" pageNumber="47" pagination="8 - 18" refId="ref5312" refString="Yuasa, H. &amp; Maekawa, F. (1976) Chromosome of Asarum and Heterotropa (Aristolochiaceae) in the Ryukyu Islands. Kromosomo II: 8 - 18." type="journal article" year="1976">Yuasa &amp; Maekawa 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,747,2077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,510,1662,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Morphological comparison:</emphasis>
―Morphologically, the pyriform perianth tube and the complex reticulation pattern on the inner surface of the perianth tube show that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2014" box="[653,837,1698,1724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ampulliflorum">
<emphasis box="[653,837,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. ampulliflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Morr. et Decne.) F. Maekawa" authorityName="F. Maekawa" baseAuthorityName="Morr. et Decne." box="[977,1447,1698,1724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asaroides">
<emphasis box="[977,1111,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. asaroides</emphasis>
(Morr. et Decne.) F. Maekawa
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hooker" authorityName="Hooker" box="[136,398,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macranthum">
<emphasis box="[136,307,1733,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. macranthum</emphasis>
Hooker
</taxonomicName>
f., and 
<taxonomicName authority="F. Maekawa" authorityName="F. Maekawa" box="[490,791,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="satsumense">
<emphasis box="[490,646,1733,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. satsumense</emphasis>
F. Maekawa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[865,926,1733,1759]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Japan</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1051,1733,1759]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2014" box="[1180,1368,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ampulliflorum">
<emphasis box="[1180,1368,1733,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. ampulliflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the latter three species by the leaf shape and size, ratio of the perianth tube length to the diameter of the widest points of perianth tube (
<figureCitation box="[463,526,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1437,1459]" captionTargetBox="[195,1413,219,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,190,1413]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A histogram showing differences in the ratio of the perianth tube length to the diameter at the widest points of perianth tube and the ratio of the perianth tube length to limb-lobe length among Asarum ampulliflorum (am), A. asaroides (as), A. macranthum (ma), and A. satsumense (sa). The lines in the plot indicated the range of each character from each species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), ratio of the perianth-tube length to limb-lobe length (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1166,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1437,1459]" captionTargetBox="[195,1413,219,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,190,1413]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A histogram showing differences in the ratio of the perianth tube length to the diameter at the widest points of perianth tube and the ratio of the perianth tube length to limb-lobe length among Asarum ampulliflorum (am), A. asaroides (as), A. macranthum (ma), and A. satsumense (sa). The lines in the plot indicated the range of each character from each species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), color of the inner surface of the perianth tube, stigma, and stylar protuberance shape (
<figureCitation box="[780,846,1838,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,805,827]" captionTargetBox="[191,1373,455,733]" captionTargetId="figure-118@5.[151,1436,389,780]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Comparison of stigma and style morphology of Asarum ampulliflorum (A), A. asaroides (B), A. macranthum (C), and A. satsumense (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146480/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2014" box="[866,1111,1838,1865]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ampulliflorum">
<emphasis box="[866,1111,1838,1865]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Asarum ampulliflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1445,1838,1865]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asaroides">
<emphasis box="[1311,1445,1838,1865]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. asaroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, it differs from the latter by having cordate to triangular-ovate (vs. widely ovate to ovate triangular) leaves, small flowers (the widest diam. of perianth tube &lt;
<quantity box="[602,676,1909,1935]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
vs.&gt; 
<quantity box="[732,809,1909,1935]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
) and long limb lobes (ratio of tube length to limb-lobe length 0.86–1.21 vs. 1.67–2.0). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2014" box="[401,645,1944,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ampulliflorum">
<emphasis box="[401,645,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Asarum ampulliflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[812,979,1944,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macranthum">
<emphasis box="[812,979,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. macranthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1180,1944,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Asarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="satsumense">
<emphasis box="[1029,1180,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">A. satsumense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated from the latter two by its lacrymiform (vs. unciform) stigma and 2-lobed stylar protuberance with a broadened wing on each side (vs. 2-lobed, with a horn-like protuberance on each side). The detailed differences of these four species are shown in Table 1. In addition, we provide a key to these four closely related species to aid in identification.
</paragraph>
